---
import { getRelativeLocaleUrl } from "astro:i18n";
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "@/components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "@/components/Footer.astro";
import NewsletterSignup from "@/components/NewsletterSignup.astro";
import Socials from "@/components/Socials.astro";
import { useTranslations } from "@/i18n";
import config from "@/config";

const { socials } = config;

const locale = Astro.currentLocale ?? config.site.lang;
const t = useTranslations(locale);
const homePath = getRelativeLocaleUrl(locale, "");
---

<Layout>
  <Header />
  <main
    id="main-content"
    data-layout="index"
    data-home-path={homePath}
    class="app-layout"
  >
    <section id="hero" class="border-border border-b pt-10 pb-12 sm:pt-12 sm:pb-16 space-y-10">
      
      <img src="/one-more-island-book-min.jpg"
           alt="One More Island book cover"
           class="mx-auto block w-1/3 max-w-xs rounded-lg shadow-lg"
      />

      <div class="mx-auto max-w-prose space-y-6 text-base leading-8 text-foreground/90 text-justify">
        <p> 
        Peter Watchett is adrift in Sandport – a man navigating the currents of his own life and mortality
        with secrets he’s never told himself and a past haunted by the choices of the past. His work feels like a
        shield against ghosts from London, but when his brother Zak returns unexpectedly, carrying echoes not just of
        their shared history but potentially crucial truths about Peter’s own absent biological father and
        Morgan – the daughter he's never met – the protective walls begin to crumble.
        </p>
        <p>
        Peter finds an uneasy peace on the Kent coast, drawn back by forces both familial and deeper. He must
        confront the lies that shaped his identity: Isla’s distance, his step father's kindness, Zak's enigmatic
        silence about Alice, Morgan, and the tumultuous years surrounding their earlier endeavours.
        </p>
        <p>
        As he reconnects with his family – wrestling with anger towards Isla, navigating the complexities of Zak's return,
        and facing the immense challenge of building a relationship with Morgan – Peter
        discovers that finding himself involves charting new territory. His journey back to Sandport wasn't just about
        returning home; it’s the final leg in uncovering the fragmented truth of his life, reconciling past losses, and
        perhaps finally learning to find peace with himself.
      </p>    
      <p>
        This poignant novel explores the difficult work of finding your way back to people you've lost and those
        standing right before you, set against the backdrop of London's pressures and Kent’s coastal serenity. A story of
        complex fatherhood, enduring family bonds (found or broken), and the search for peace through confronting one's
        history.
      </p>

        <p>
          One More Island is the new novel from Richard W. Bown. Coming early 2027.
        </p>

        <p>
          Sign up below to get book news, writing updates, and launch information straight to your inbox.
        </p>
      </div>

      <section id="newsletter" class="mt-12 sm:mt-16">
        <NewsletterSignup title="Sign up for updates" description="Get book news, writing updates, and launch information straight to your inbox." />
      </section>
    </section>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </Layout>

<script>
  document.addEventListener("astro:page-load", () => {
    const indexLayout = (document.querySelector("#main-content") as HTMLElement)
      ?.dataset;
    const baseRoot = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/?$/, "/");
    if (indexLayout?.layout) {
      sessionStorage.setItem("backUrl", indexLayout.homePath ?? baseRoot);
    }
  });
</script>
